//axhrb_regime
{rbrn_regime}

This regime specifies variables that define crucible deployment configurations within the Recipe Bottle system.
Each
{rbrn_regime}
instance represents a distinct service deployment with its own network, entry, and uplink settings.
RBRN assignment files are found in `.rbk/{moniker}/rbrn.env` and configure container deployment and network security.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_moniker}

Unique moniker for the crucible instance.
Must be 2-12 characters and form a valid cross-context identifier.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_description}

Human-readable description of the service purpose.
Optional; 0-120 characters.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_runtime}

Container runtime for service deployment.
Must be
{rbrn_runtime_docker}
or
{rbrn_runtime_podman}.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrn_group_ark_reference}

Ark references identify which vessel hallmark to deploy.
At runtime, these resolve against the repository configuration to form complete image paths.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrn_sentry_vessel}

Vessel identifier for the sentry container image.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrn_sentry_hallmark}

Hallmark timestamp for the sentry container image.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrn_bottle_vessel}

Vessel identifier for the bottle container image.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrn_bottle_hallmark}

Hallmark timestamp for the bottle container image.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrn_group_service_readiness}

Service readiness configuration controls post-charge wait behavior for bottle services that need warmup time before responding to traffic.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrn_bottle_readiness_delay_sec}

Seconds to wait after compose-up returns before the charge tabtarget completes.
A fixed sleep, not a probe — generous values are cheap and reliable.
Set to 0 when the bottle has no warmup phase (e.g., adversarial-only nameplates).

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_entry_mode}

Selects entry service behavior for user-initiated connections.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrn_group_entry}

//axhrgc_gate
{rbrn_entry_mode}
{rbrn_entry_mode_enabled}

Variables in this group apply only when
{rbrn_entry_mode}
is
{rbrn_entry_mode_enabled}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrn_entry_port_workstation}

External port exposed on the transit network for user entry.
Must be less than
{rbrn_uplink_port_min}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrn_entry_port_enclave}

Port used between sentry and bottle containers for entry traffic.
Must be less than
{rbrn_uplink_port_min}.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_enclave_base_ip}

Base IPv4 address that defines the enclave network range.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_enclave_netmask}

Network mask width for the enclave network addressing.
Valid range: 8-30.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_enclave_sentry_ip}

IP address assigned to the sentry container for traffic mediation within the enclave.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_enclave_bottle_ip}

IP address assigned to the bottle container within the enclave.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_uplink_port_min}

Minimum port number for bottle-initiated outbound connections.
Must be greater than any entry port.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_uplink_dns_mode}

Selects DNS resolution behavior for bottle-initiated requests.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrn_uplink_access_mode}

Selects IP access behavior for bottle-initiated connections.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrn_group_access_allowlist}

//axhrgc_gate
{rbrn_uplink_access_mode}
{rbrn_uplink_access_mode_allowlist}

Variables in this group apply only when
{rbrn_uplink_access_mode}
is
{rbrn_uplink_access_mode_allowlist}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrn_uplink_allowed_cidrs}

CIDR ranges for allowed bottle-initiated outbound traffic.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrn_group_dns_allowlist}

//axhrgc_gate
{rbrn_uplink_dns_mode}
{rbrn_uplink_dns_mode_allowlist}

Variables in this group apply only when
{rbrn_uplink_dns_mode}
is
{rbrn_uplink_dns_mode_allowlist}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrn_uplink_allowed_domains}

Domain names allowed for bottle-initiated DNS resolution.

// Volume mount specifications relocated to per-nameplate compose fragments ({moniker}.compose.yml).

//axhro_kindle
{rbkro_kindle}

Sets defaults for all RBRN_ variables via `VAR="${VAR:-}"` pattern.
Detects unexpected RBRN_ variables via compgen prefix scan.
Builds ZRBRN_ROLLUP serialization string and ZRBRN_DOCKER_ENV injection array.

//axhro_validate
{rbkro_validate}

Validates fields via buv_env_* type checkers.
Validates RBRN_RUNTIME, RBRN_ENTRY_MODE, RBRN_UPLINK_DNS_MODE, RBRN_UPLINK_ACCESS_MODE enum constraints.
Conditional validation: entry ports when ENTRY_MODE=enabled, allowlists when *_MODE=allowlist.

//axhro_render
{rbkro_render}

Renders via rbcr_* shared module with gate-aware section suppression.
Sections: Core Service Identity, Container Image Configuration, Entry Service Configuration (gated), Enclave Network, Uplink Core, DNS Allowlist (gated), Access Allowlist (gated).
Displays unexpected variables in red.
Validates after full render completes.

//axhro_list
{rbkro_list}

Enumerates available nameplate instances by scanning assignment files matching the RBRN naming pattern.
Returns moniker identifiers suitable for instance selection.

//axhro_survey
{rbkro_survey}

Read-only cross-instance summary of all nameplates.
Iterates rbrn_list, kindles each instance in a subshell to avoid sentinel conflicts.
Displays network topology, entry configuration, and local image availability for all instances.

//axhro_audit
{rbkro_audit}

Cross-instance validation of all nameplates plus external verification.
Performs survey display, then validates cross-instance constraints: port uniqueness, subnet non-overlap, IP uniqueness.
Includes GCB quota headroom check via Service Usage API.

//axhrb_regime
{rbrd_regime}

This regime specifies depot-time-immutable identity and infrastructure settings.
Each
{rbrd_regime}
instance pins the values that
{rbtgo_depot_levy}
consumes at depot creation — the identity tuple `(RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER)` (from which depot project ID, GAR repository, pool stem, and bucket fall out as RBDC constants), the GCP region, and the Cloud Build private worker pool machine type.
RBRD assignment files are found in the operator's local filesystem (typically `.rbk/rbrd.env`) and are frozen for the productive lifetime of the depot.
Changing any field after levy requires a fresh depot.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrd_group_depot_identity}

The cloud-namespace identity tuple consumed by
{rbtgo_depot_levy}
to derive every depot-scoped GCP resource name.
Both fields must be populated — the marshal-zero path blanks them so a fresh regime requires an explicit operator decision before `rbrd_validate` passes.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrd_cloud_prefix}

Prefix prepended to all cloud-visible resource names under the depot: GAR image paths, vessel package names,
{gcb_service}
substitutions, and other GCP-scoped identifiers.
Must be 2–11 characters, start with a lowercase letter, and end with a hyphen (regex `^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*-$`).

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrd_depot_moniker}

Stem identifier that combines with
{rbrd_cloud_prefix}
to form the depot identity tuple.
Must be 1–26 characters, start with a lowercase letter, and contain only lowercase alphanumerics (regex `^[a-z][a-z0-9]*$`).
The tuple derives `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`, `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`, `RBDC_GCB_POOL_STEM`, and `RBDC_GCS_BUCKET` at kindle time.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrd_group_region}

The default
{gcp_service}
region for regional services like
{gar_service}
and
{gcb_service}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrd_gcp_region}

Applied when creating repositories and submitting builds unless overridden by operation-specific configuration.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrd_group_pool}

{gcb_service}
private worker pool configuration consumed at pool creation time by
{rbtgo_depot_levy}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrd_gcb_machine_type}

Compute Engine machine type for the private worker pool.
Valid families: `e2`, `n2d`, `c3`.
Examples: `e2-standard-2`, `e2-highcpu-8`, `n2d-standard-4`.
Pool scales to zero workers when idle — no idle cost accrues.

//axhro_kindle
{rbkro_kindle}

Kindles the {rbrd_regime} fields by enrolling each field with its type-specific constraints under named groups.
Detects unexpected RBRD_ variables.
Locks the regime against further modification.

//axhro_validate
{rbkro_validate}

Validates enrolled fields against type-specific constraints from enrollment.
Enforces format constraints on {rbrd_cloud_prefix} and {rbrd_depot_moniker}, and the joint-length cap on `${RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (≤30 chars per the GCP project ID limit).

//axhro_render
{rbkro_render}

Renders the {rbrd_regime} grouped by section with presentation gates per group.
Sections: Depot Identity, GCP Region, Google Cloud Build Pool.

[[rbrd_tripwire]]
{rbrd_tripwire}::
A `FROM scratch` GAR image carrying the verbatim `.rbk/rbrd.env` assignment file, inscribed at `«REGION»-docker.pkg.dev/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/«GAR_REPOSITORY»/rbi_df/rbrd:tripwire`.
The tripwire makes the depot-time-immutable contract enforceable: because every RBDC-derived resource name (project ID, GAR repository, pool stem, bucket) is computed from the {rbrd_regime} at kindle time, a silent post-levy edit of `.rbk/rbrd.env` would point subsequent operations at a different depot identity or worker-pool configuration than the one actually provisioned.
+
The tripwire is _produced_ exactly once, host-side, at the tail of
{rbtgo_depot_levy}
— after the depot-tracking refresh, using the Payor OAuth access token already in scope.
A pre-push existence guard (`docker manifest inspect`) makes inscription idempotent-by-refusal: an already-present tripwire is fatal, since RBRD is frozen for the depot's productive lifetime and refreshing it requires a fresh depot (unmake + relevy).
+
The tripwire is _consumed_ inline by every cloud-submitting command before it dispatches a build: the command pulls the image, extracts `/rbrd.env`, and exact-byte-compares it (comments, whitespace, and line ordering all participate) against the local `.rbk/rbrd.env`.
A mismatch, a missing image, or a registry/auth failure is fatal with recovery guidance — the command refuses to submit cloud work against a drifted or unverifiable depot regime.
The check takes a bearer token parameter and is role-agnostic; each consuming command passes its own role's token (no new IAM grants).
+
The tripwire is depot-scoped operational state, not part of the hallmark / reliquary / enshrine image catalogue; the image enumerators ignore the `rbi_df` namespace by design.
Both operations are implemented host-side (Cloud Build is not involved) by `rbrd_inscribe` and `rbrd_check` in `Tools/rbk/rbndb_base.sh`, exposed for manual use via the `rbw-rdi` (inscribe) and `rbw-rdc` (check) tabtargets.

