//axhrb_regime
{rbrm_regime}

This regime specifies Podman VM supply chain configuration within the Recipe Bottle system.
Each
{rbrm_regime}
instance represents the operator's chosen Podman release, platform targets, and supporting tool versions.
RBRM assignment files are found at `rbmm_moorings/rbrm.env`.
Podman VM support is currently deferred.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrm_crane_tar_gz}

Path to crane tool tarball archive.
Crane is used for OCI image manipulation and registry operations within the Podman VM.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrm_manifest_platforms}

Space-separated list of platforms for multi-platform manifest creation.
Example: `mow_x86_64_wsl mow_aarch64_wsl`.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrm_chosen_podman_version}

Podman version string for VM provisioning and build operations.
Must match a valid Podman release version (N.N or N.N.N format).

//axhrv_variable
{rbrm_chosen_vmimage_origin}

Podman VM image origin specification.
Determines which VM base image to use for machine creation.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrm_chosen_identity}

Identity specification for VM or build environment.
Used to configure authentication and authorization context.

//axhro_kindle
{rbkro_kindle}

Enrolls all RBRM_ variables via buv enrollment.
Guards against unexpected RBRM_ variables via scope sentinel.
Locks all enrolled variables against mutation.

//axhro_validate
{rbkro_validate}

Validates fields via buv_vet type checkers.
Validates platform format constraints (lowercase alphanumeric with underscores).
Validates Podman version format (semantic version).

//axhro_render
{rbkro_render}

Renders via buv_render.
Sections: Podman VM Supply Chain.

//axhrb_regime
{rbrr_regime}

This regime specifies variables that define repository-wide configuration and installation-wide settings within the Recipe Bottle system.
Each
{rbrr_regime}
instance represents foundational infrastructure configuration that rarely changes and is shared across all Recipe Bottle operations.
RBRR assignment files are found in the operator's local filesystem (typically `rbmm_moorings/rbrr.env`) and configure the runtime container prefix, vessel directory, container DNS, Cloud Build timeouts, secrets directory, and public docs URL.
Depot-time-immutable identity and pool configuration live in the sibling
{rbrd_regime}.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrr_group_resource_prefixing}

Operator-chosen identifier that scopes machine-local resource names — container names, Docker network names, and other runtime identifiers on the operator's workstation.
Enables multi-regime isolation on shared infrastructure — distinct developers can coexist on the same workstation without name collisions.
Must be populated — the marshal-zero path blanks it so a fresh regime requires an explicit operator decision before `rbrr_validate` passes.
Must be 2–11 characters, start with a lowercase letter, and end with a hyphen (regex `^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*-$`).

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_runtime_prefix}

Prefix prepended to machine-local resource names: container names, Docker network names, and other runtime identifiers on the operator's workstation.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrr_group_service_accounts}

Credential file paths derived from a single enrolled directory for each operational role.
Each RBRA file contains the minimum identity and signing material needed for authentication to
{gcp_service}
via service account.
The payor RBRO file contains OAuth refresh credentials for
{rbtr_payor}
operations.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_secrets_dir}

Directory on the operator's local filesystem outside the source repository that contains all credential files.
Enrolled and validated to exist; individual file paths are derived from this directory at lock time.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_retriever_rbra_file}

Path derived from
{rbrr_secrets_dir}
as `retriever/rbra.env`.
Enables the operator to assume the retriever role for container image operations.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_director_rbra_file}

Path derived from
{rbrr_secrets_dir}
as `director/rbra.env`.
Enables the operator to assume the director role for build submission and image management operations.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_governor_rbra_file}

Path derived from
{rbrr_secrets_dir}
as `governor/rbra.env`.
Enables the operator to assume the governor role for
{gcp_project_id}
administration operations.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_payor_rbro_file}

Path derived from
{rbrr_secrets_dir}
as `payor/rbro.env`.
Enables the operator to perform
{rbtr_payor}
OAuth operations using locally stored refresh credentials.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrr_group_container_runtime}

Variables that configure container runtime and deployment environment settings.
These settings control DNS resolution and vessel directory layout.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_vessel_dir}

Directory path containing vessel configuration subdirectories.
Each subdirectory defines a vessel image source (bind or conjure mode).

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_dns_server}

DNS server IP address used by sentry containers for name resolution.
Injected into container environment to control DNS behavior.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrr_group_build_configuration}

Operator-chosen
{gcb_service}
build parameters that may change across builds within a depot's lifetime.
Depot-time-immutable machine type lives in the
{rbrd_regime}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_gcb_min_concurrent_builds}

Minimum number of concurrent Cloud Build executions required.
With private pools, the relevant quota metric is `concurrent_private_pool_build_cpus` on the pool's host project.
Machine type is determined by the pool configuration at creation time, not by individual build requests.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_gcb_timeout}

Maximum duration for Cloud Build operations before timeout.
Specified in seconds or duration format (e.g., `3600s`).

//axhrgb_group
{rbrr_group_public_docs}

Public documentation URL for user-facing references.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_public_docs_url}

Complete URL for the public documentation entry point.
Updated per-release (swap branch name) or per-incorporation (point at a fork).
Used by buh_tlt glossary links and user-facing output.

//axhro_kindle
{rbkro_kindle}

Kindles the {rbrr_regime} fields by enrolling each field with its type-specific constraints under named groups.
Detects unexpected RBRR_ variables.
Composes the docker environment injection set and locks the regime against further modification.

//axhro_validate
{rbkro_validate}

Validates enrolled fields against type-specific constraints from enrollment.
Validates directory existence for {rbrr_vessel_dir} and {rbrr_secrets_dir}.
Enforces format constraints on {rbrr_runtime_prefix}.

//axhro_render
{rbkro_render}

Renders the {rbrr_regime} grouped by section with presentation gates per group.
Sections: Runtime Prefix, Vessel and Local Configuration, Google Cloud Build Configuration, Secrets Directory, Public Docs.

//axhrb_regime
{rbrd_regime}

This regime specifies depot-time-immutable identity and infrastructure settings.
Each
{rbrd_regime}
instance pins the values that
{rbtgo_depot_levy}
consumes at depot creation — the identity tuple `(RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER)` (from which depot project ID, GAR repository, pool stem, and bucket fall out as RBDC constants), the GCP region, and the Cloud Build private worker pool machine type.
RBRD assignment files are found in the operator's local filesystem (typically `rbmm_moorings/rbrd.env`) and are frozen for the productive lifetime of the depot.
Changing any field after levy requires a fresh depot.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrd_group_depot_identity}

The cloud-namespace identity tuple consumed by
{rbtgo_depot_levy}
to derive every depot-scoped GCP resource name.
Both fields must be populated — the marshal-zero path blanks them so a fresh regime requires an explicit operator decision before `rbrd_validate` passes.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrd_cloud_prefix}

Prefix prepended to all cloud-visible resource names under the depot: GAR image paths, vessel package names,
{gcb_service}
substitutions, and other GCP-scoped identifiers.
Must be 2–11 characters, start with a lowercase letter, and end with a hyphen (regex `^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*-$`).

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrd_depot_moniker}

Stem identifier that combines with
{rbrd_cloud_prefix}
to form the depot identity tuple.
Must be 1–26 characters, start with a lowercase letter, and contain only lowercase alphanumerics (regex `^[a-z][a-z0-9]*$`).
The tuple derives `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`, `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`, `RBDC_GCB_POOL_STEM`, and `RBDC_GCS_BUCKET` at kindle time.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrd_group_region}

The default
{gcp_service}
region for regional services like
{gar_service}
and
{gcb_service}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrd_gcp_region}

Applied when creating repositories and submitting builds unless overridden by operation-specific configuration.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrd_group_pool}

{gcb_service}
private worker pool configuration consumed at pool creation time by
{rbtgo_depot_levy}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrd_gcb_machine_type}

Compute Engine machine type for the private worker pool.
Valid families: `e2`, `n2d`, `c3`.
Examples: `e2-standard-2`, `e2-highcpu-8`, `n2d-standard-4`.
Pool scales to zero workers when idle — no idle cost accrues.

//axhro_kindle
{rbkro_kindle}

Kindles the {rbrd_regime} fields by enrolling each field with its type-specific constraints under named groups.
Detects unexpected RBRD_ variables.
Locks the regime against further modification.

//axhro_validate
{rbkro_validate}

Validates enrolled fields against type-specific constraints from enrollment.
Enforces format constraints on {rbrd_cloud_prefix} and {rbrd_depot_moniker}, and the joint-length cap on `${RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (≤30 chars per the GCP project ID limit).

//axhro_render
{rbkro_render}

Renders the {rbrd_regime} grouped by section with presentation gates per group.
Sections: Depot Identity, GCP Region, Google Cloud Build Pool.

[[rbrd_tripwire]]
{rbrd_tripwire}::
A `FROM scratch` GAR image carrying the verbatim `rbmm_moorings/rbrd.env` assignment file, inscribed at `«REGION»-docker.pkg.dev/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/«GAR_REPOSITORY»/rbi_df/rbrd:tripwire`.
The tripwire makes the depot-time-immutable contract enforceable: because every RBDC-derived resource name (project ID, GAR repository, pool stem, bucket) is computed from the {rbrd_regime} at kindle time, a silent post-levy edit of `rbmm_moorings/rbrd.env` would point subsequent operations at a different depot identity or worker-pool configuration than the one actually provisioned.
+
The tripwire is _produced_ exactly once, host-side, at the tail of
{rbtgo_depot_levy}
— after the depot-tracking refresh, using the Payor OAuth access token already in scope.
A pre-push existence guard (`docker manifest inspect`) makes inscription idempotent-by-refusal: an already-present tripwire is fatal, since RBRD is frozen for the depot's productive lifetime and refreshing it requires a fresh depot (unmake + relevy).
+
The tripwire is _consumed_ inline by every cloud-submitting command before it dispatches a build: the command pulls the image, extracts `/rbrd.env`, and exact-byte-compares it (comments, whitespace, and line ordering all participate) against the local `rbmm_moorings/rbrd.env`.
A mismatch, a missing image, or a registry/auth failure is fatal with recovery guidance — the command refuses to submit cloud work against a drifted or unverifiable depot regime.
The check takes a bearer token parameter and is role-agnostic; each consuming command passes its own role's token (no new IAM grants).
+
The tripwire is depot-scoped operational state, not part of the hallmark / reliquary / enshrine image catalogue; the image enumerators ignore the `rbi_df` namespace by design.
Both operations are implemented host-side (Cloud Build is not involved) by `rbrd_inscribe` and `rbrd_check` in `Tools/rbk/rbndb_base.sh`, exposed for manual use via the `rbw-rdi` (inscribe) and `rbw-rdc` (check) tabtargets.

